# Commit and Deploy Workflow

For this project, every code change must be committed and pushed without asking the user first.

After pushing to `main`:

1. Commit with a clear message describing why the change was made.
2. Push to `origin main`.
3. Poll the latest GitHub Actions run (`gh run list` then `gh run watch <run-id> --exit-status`) until it completes.
4. Report back to the user with commit hash, run status (success/failure), and deploy duration when relevant.

Do not leave uncommitted work at the end of a task unless the user explicitly says not to deploy.

Production URL: https://problems4us.com
